The paper deals with the task of predicting relative attributes from images, which is a problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep neural network architecture for this task, which involves learning features and ranking images based on these features. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
